"You're not going to go out and get a haul like you see on the TV show your first time out," Fobes says. "It just isn't going to happen. Be realistic." Starting small has its benefits, she adds. Using only a few coupons at first will help familiarize you with reading coupons (online and paper) and looking for expiration dates or store limitations.
